To replicate the chart shown in the image using LaTeX and TikZ, you can use the following code:

```latex
\documentclass{standalone}
\usepackage{pgfplots}
\pgfplotsset{compat=1.17}

\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}
    \begin{axis}[
        width=10cm, height=8cm,
        xlabel={\# of Turkish Tokens},
        ylabel={English \& Turkish ARC Acc.},
        ymin=30, ymax=65,
        xmin=0, xmax=7,
        xtick={0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6},
        xticklabels={0, 50M, 130M, 250M, 0.5B, 1.1B, 2.5B},
        ytick={30, 35, 40, 45, 50, 55, 60, 65},
        grid=major,
        legend style={at={(0.5,-0.15)}, anchor=north, legend columns=-1},
        legend cell align={left},
        title={Comparison of ARC Scores of Mistral Model}
    ]

    % ARC-tr Acc.
    \addplot[
        color=blue,
        mark=o,
        thick
    ]
    coordinates {
        (0,35)(1,35.5)(2,36)(3,36.5)(4,37)(5,38)(6,39)
    };
    \addlegendentry{ARC-tr Acc.}

    % ARC-eng Acc.
    \addplot[
        color=red,
        mark=square,
        thick
    ]
    coordinates {
        (0,60)(1,56)(2,52)(3,48)(4,45)(5,42)(6,40)
    };
    \addlegendentry{ARC-eng Acc.}

    \end{axis}
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{document}
```

### Explanation:
- **Axis Configuration:** The axis is set to display the number of Turkish tokens on the x-axis and the ARC accuracy on the y-axis.
- **Plot Styles:** Different colors and markers are used for the ARC-tr (Turkish) and ARC-eng (English) accuracies.
- **Legend and Title:** A legend is included to differentiate between the two datasets, and a title is provided at the top.
- **Data Points:** The coordinates represent the data points for each respective line in the plot. Adjust these values if the actual data differs.

This code should recreate the chart as shown in the image. Make sure you have the `pgfplots` package available to compile this code.

